<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="333" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1595,2018]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,347,1739,1765]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">Description:</emphasis>
dark gray crown and nape; gray sides of head; rufous dark brown upperparts, subtly vermiculated with black; ochraceous-brown chest; buff belly; buff flanks and undertail coverts, barred with black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="333" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1595,2018]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1811,1837]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: can be separated from 
<taxonomicName authority="obsoletus" authorityName="obsoletus (Temminck" authorityYear="1815" box="[581,947,1811,1837]" class="Aves" family="Tinamidae" genus="Crypturellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tinamiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="obsoletus" subSpecies="obsoletus">
<emphasis box="[581,947,1811,1837]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">Crypturellus obsoletus obsoletus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other taxa of the complex by having an ochraceous chest and pale-brown belly. It also has a distinct vocal pattern, with a series of 2‒6 notes, not ascending or accelerating.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1595,2018]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1919,1945]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">Voice:</emphasis>
emits a single note, similar to a human whistle. Produces a long series of more than 10 notes, ascending in the end. It also produces a shorter series of 2‒6 notes that neither ascend nor accelerate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="334" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1595,2018]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1437,150,429]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="334" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,355,1991,2017]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">Distribution:</emphasis>
a Brazilian endemic, found in the Amazon basin in the states of 
<collectingRegion box="[1072,1184,1991,2017]" country="Brazil" name="Rondonia" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">Rondônia</collectingRegion>
, from the eastern bank of Madeira river west to Xingu river. The southwestern limit is in the Guaporé river, extending to the east to northern 
<collectingRegion box="[151,299,186,213]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
, in the Alta Floresta region. In 
<collectingRegion box="[646,699,186,212]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">Pará</collectingRegion>
, there are populations in the south (Serra do Cachimbo) and north (Santarém), with literature records from the east (Serra dos Carajás).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="334" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,150,429]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,258,284]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">Remarks:</emphasis>
considered as a full species due to the morphological and vocal differences when compared to other taxa of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1815" box="[279,533,294,320]" class="Aves" family="Tinamidae" genus="Crypturellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tinamiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obsoletus">
<emphasis box="[279,533,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">Crypturellus obsoletus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex. Based on the data presented herein, 
<emphasis box="[1061,1280,294,321]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">C. o. hypochraceus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Miranda-Ribeiro, A." pageId="13" pageNumber="334" pagination="667 - 788" refId="ref11400" refString="Miranda-Ribeiro, A. (1938) Notas ornithologicas (XIII): Tinamidae. Revista do Museo Paulista, 23, 667 - 788." type="journal article" year="1938">Miranda-Ribeiro, 1938</bibRefCitation>
) represents a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Salvadori, 1895)" authorityName="Illiger" authorityYear="1811" baseAuthorityName="Salvadori" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[649,1027,330,357]" class="Aves" family="Tinamidae" genus="Crypturus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Tinamiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="griseiventris">
<emphasis box="[649,822,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">C. griseiventris</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Salvadori, T." box="[836,1019,330,357]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" pagination="1 - 636" refId="ref12143" refString="Salvadori, T. (1895) Catalogue of the Chenomorphae (Palamedeae, Phoenicopteri, Anseres), Crypturi and Ratitae in the collection of the British Museum. Catalogue of the Birds in the British Museum, 27, 1 - 636. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8233" type="journal article" year="1895">Salvadori, 1895</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
